I"Ð<p>This important new book provides a comprehensive, exam orientated clinical anatomy book for anaesthetists preparing for all parts of the FRCA exam.</p>

<p>It covers all body regions, relating underlying anatomy to practical procedures and anatomical principles, spanning the breadth of the curriculum and comprising exam-style questions:</p>

<p>SAQ questions
OSCE stations
SOE questions
MCQs.</p>

<p>The text is highly illustrated in full colour with ultrasound images, diagrams and photographs of cadaveric material and models.</p>

<p>This is the first anatomy book specifically orientated for the FRCA exam, making it an essential resource for anaesthetists preparing for all parts of the FRCA examination.</p>
